  "body": "**Is this a BUG REPORT or FEATURE REQUEST?**:\r\nBUG\r\n/kind bug\r\n\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\nInvalid azure disk URIs is not cleared and it keeps other disk attach fail.\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\nThe bad request should be cleared so it shouldn't block other disk attach\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\n\r\nCreate Pod A with bad URI\r\n```yaml\r\n # <other stuff removed>\r\n  volumes:\r\n      - name: bad-disk\r\n        azureDisk:\r\n          diskName: bad-disk\r\n          diskURI: https://storageaccount.blob.core.windows.net/vhds/do-not-exist.vhd\r\n```\r\nPod A keeps spinning at ContainerCreate.\r\n\r\nThen Create Pod B with good URI, Pod B stucks.\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`): 1.10\r\n- Cloud provider or hardware configuration: Azure\r\n- OS (e.g. from /etc/os-release):\r\n- Kernel (e.g. `uname -a`):\r\n- Install tools:\r\n- Others:\r\n",
